                <h2 id="express-entry">Express Entry Timeline (Without PNP)</h2>
                <p>
                    If you have a high enough Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS) score to receive an
                    Invitation to Apply (ITA) without a provincial nomination, Express Entry is the
                    fastest pathway to Canadian PR.
                </p>

                <h3>Current CRS Requirements (2026)</h3>
                <p>
                    In 2026, CRS cutoffs have varied based on draw type:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Canadian Experience Class (CEC):</strong> 509-511</li>
                    <li><strong>All-program draws:</strong> 520-540 (when held)</li>
                    <li><strong>Category-based draws:</strong> 379-510 depending on category</li>
                    <li><strong>PNP draws:</strong> 711-746 (includes 600 nomination points)</li>
                </ul>

