                </p>

                <h3>Category-Based Selection: A Faster Path?</h3>
                <p>
                    In 2026, IRCC continues category-based Express Entry draws targeting specific groups:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>French language proficiency</strong> — CRS as low as 379</li>
                    <li><strong>Healthcare occupations</strong> — CRS 462-510</li>
                    <li><strong>STEM occupations</strong> — Priority draws</li>
                    <li><strong>Trade occupations</strong> — Priority draws</li>
                    <li><strong>Agriculture workers</strong> — Priority draws</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    If you qualify for a category-based draw, you may receive an ITA with a lower CRS
                    score than general draws require, significantly shortening your timeline.
                </p>

                <h2 id="other-pathways">Other PR Pathways and Their Timelines</h2>

                <h3>Family Sponsorship (Spousal)</h3>
                <p>
                    If you have a Canadian citizen or permanent resident spouse, family sponsorship
                    is an option. Current processing times:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Spouse living inside Canada:</strong> 12-15 months</li>
                    <li><strong>Spouse living outside Canada:</strong> 12-18 months</li>
                </ul>

