                <h2 id="factors">Factors That Affect Processing Time</h2>
                <p>
                    Several factors can speed up or slow down your PR timeline:
                </p>

                <h3>Factors That Speed Up Processing</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Complete application:</strong> Missing documents cause delays. Submit everything upfront.</li>
                    <li><strong>Express Entry pathway:</strong> Always faster than paper-based processing.</li>
                    <li><strong>Tech or healthcare occupation:</strong> Often receive priority processing.</li>
                    <li><strong>Simple case:</strong> Single applicants with straightforward work history process faster.</li>
                    <li><strong>Upfront medicals:</strong> Completing medical exams before requested can save time.</li>
                    <li><strong>Biometrics already on file:</strong> From previous visa applications.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Factors That Slow Down Processing</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Incomplete documents:</strong> Triggers procedural fairness letters and delays.</li>
                    <li><strong>Complex family situation:</strong> Multiple dependents, previous marriages, custody issues.</li>
                    <li><strong>Security concerns:</strong> Certain nationalities or work histories trigger extended background checks.</li>
                    <li><strong>Medical issues:</strong> Conditions requiring further assessment delay processing.</li>
                    <li><strong>High-volume periods:</strong> Year-end and post-policy-change periods see backlogs.</li>
                    <li><strong>Address or employment changes:</strong> Updates during processing can reset timelines.</li>
                </ul>

